<plot>An American businessman traveling in Japan must find a way to make himself understood using only travel book phrases. The problem is the Japanese businessman is also using phrases from the same source. If they can't find a way to really talk to each other, it leads to the death of everything. Thereby showing the importance and great need for meaningful dialogue between people and nations.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?397981</url></doc>
